Morrissey has written a letter to Australian retailer The Just Group imploring them to stop using angora wool . 
  The singer will be performing four shows at the Sydney Opera House in May . 
  He has banned meat products from being sold at the venue during his concerts . 
  PETA Australia have petitioned the Just Group to cease their use of the controversial fur . 
  The retailer have so far refused to back down on their stance . 
  Morrissey said he would set up petition booths at the concerts . 
 